a—Wolfe explores how biopolitics can help us understand both the ethical and political dimensions of the current questions surrounding the rights of animals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAnimal rightsxEconomic aspects. 0aAnimal rightsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aAnimal rightsxPolitical aspects. 0aSpeciesism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  alaw, litigation, legal issues, humanity, animals, relationships, biopolitical, biopolitics, animal studies, interdisciplinary, scholarship, academic, scholarly, research, researcher, theory, theoretical, critical, critique, analysis, analytical, nonhuman, rights, morals, ethics, politics, political, speciesism, carnism, economic.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226922423423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226922423/original  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles